HEADWORD: Sheld
<hw>Sheld</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE., fr.
<ets>sheld</ets> a shield, probably in allusion to the ornamentation of
shields. See <er>Shield</er>.]</ety> <def>Variegated; spotted; speckled;
piebald.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

